theorem Topology.eq_empty_of_P1_and_empty_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} (hP1 : Topology.P1 A) (hIntEmpty : interior A = (∅ : Set X)) :
    A = (∅ : Set X) := by
  classical
  -- First, we show that `A` is contained in `∅`.
  have hSub : (A : Set X) ⊆ (∅ : Set X) := by
    intro x hx
    -- From `P1` and the existence of `x ∈ A`, we obtain a point in `interior A`.
    have hIntNon : (interior A).Nonempty :=
      Topology.interior_nonempty_of_P1 (A := A) hP1 ⟨x, hx⟩
    -- But `interior A` is assumed to be empty, giving a contradiction.
    have : (∅ : Set X).Nonempty := by
      simpa [hIntEmpty] using hIntNon
    cases this
  -- Using the two-sided inclusion we obtain the desired equality.
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm hSub (Set.empty_subset _)

theorem Topology.eq_empty_of_closure_eq_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h : closure (A : Set X) = (∅ : Set X)) : A = (∅ : Set X) := by
  -- We show the two inclusions to obtain the desired set equality.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `A ⊆ ∅`
    intro x hxA
    -- Every element of `A` lies in `closure A`.
    have hx_closure : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X) := subset_closure hxA
    -- Rewrite using `h : closure A = ∅`.
    simpa [h] using hx_closure
  · -- `∅ ⊆ A` is trivial.
    intro x hxEmpty
    exact False.elim hxEmpty
